The last twenty successful commands are saved. You can repeat any command
in the history. You may also remove commands from the history.

To view the commands which are saved in the history:
   >!

To repeat the last command in the history:
   >!!

To repeat the 7th command in the history:
   >!7

To repeat the command which starts with a string in the history:
   >!drink

Removing commands from the history is by the history command with the
option -r followed by the range of commands to be removed. For instance,
the following removes the 3rd and the 5th throught the 8th commands:
   >history -r 3,5-8

